The paracautee signifies the true and legitimate parrot, which excels the rest in sense and do- cility, and can imitate the sounds of men and beasts with greatest ease and success. It is equal in size to a young pigeon: its feathers are green, but yellow‚ red, and 'blue on the head, wings, and tail. I had in my possession a bird of this kind, which I called Don Pedro, and which articulately pronounced many words, and even whole sentences, in the Spanish‚ Gua- rany, and Abiponian languages, and learnt to sing a little Spanish song admirably.
